def clean_df(df):
    df2 = df[0:5]
    df2[['folder','file']] = df.filename.str.split("/",expand=True) 
    df2 = df2.drop(columns=['filename', 'folder', 'up_votes', 'down_votes', 'gender', 'accent', 'duration'])
    df2 = df2[['file', 'text']]

    #Change mp3 to wav
    df2['file'] = df2['file'].str.replace('mp3','wav')

    return df2

    pathAudio = 'C:/Users/hongh/Documents/GitHub/Speech-Sentiment-Analysis-/Transcription/dataset/cv-valid-train/converted/'+audioFile

Error Rate¶

In [9]:
def error_df(df3):
    
    transformation = jiwer.Compose([
        jiwer.ToLowerCase(),
        jiwer.Strip(),
        jiwer.RemoveEmptyStrings(),
        jiwer.RemovePunctuation(),
        jiwer.RemoveMultipleSpaces(),
        jiwer.RemoveWhiteSpace(replace_by_space=False)
    ]) 
    
    df4 = df3[['file']]
    
    # word error rate (WER)
    df4['wer_python'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wer(row['text'], row['python'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1) 
    df4['wer_google'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wer(row['text'], row['google'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1)
    df4['wer_IBM'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wer(row['text'], row['IBM'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1)
    df4['wer_wit'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wer(row['text'], row['wit'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1)
    df4['wer_azure'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wer(row['text'], row['azure'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1)
    
     
    # Word Information Preserved (WIP)
    df4['wip_python'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wip(row['text'], row['python'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1) 
    df4['wip_google'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wip(row['text'], row['google'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1)
    df4['wip_IBM'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wip(row['text'], row['IBM'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1)
    df4['wip_wit'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wip(row['text'], row['wit'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1)
    df4['wip_azure'] = df3.apply(lambda row : jiwer.wip(row['text'], row['azure'], truth_transform=transformation, hypothesis_transform=transformation), axis = 1)
        
    return df4

def transcribe(path, audio_file):
    os.chdir(path)
    
    speech_key, service_region = "abfc8af0f62d45aaa5317e4290b149c0", "eastus"
    speech_config = s.SpeechConfig(subscription=speech_key, region=service_region)

    audio_config = s.audio.AudioConfig(filename=audio_file)
    speech_recognizer = s.SpeechRecognizer(speech_config=speech_config, audio_config=audio_config)
    result = speech_recognizer.recognize_once()

    text_azure = result.text
    return text_azure

sid_obj = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer() 
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(30,1)})

def visualise_sentiments(data):
  sns.heatmap(pd.DataFrame(data).set_index("Sentence").T,center=0, annot=True, cmap = "PiYG")

def VADER_sentiment_scores(sentence): 
    sentiment_dict = sid_obj.polarity_scores(sentence)   
    if sentiment_dict['compound'] >= 0.05 : 
        print("Positive",sentiment_dict['compound']) 
    elif sentiment_dict['compound'] <= - 0.05 : 
        print("Negative",sentiment_dict['compound']) 
    else : 
        print("Neutral",sentiment_dict['compound']) 
    
    
    print(sentiment_dict)

    visualise_sentiments({
        "Sentence":["SENTENCE"] + sentence.split(),
        "Sentiment":[sid_obj.polarity_scores(sentence)["compound"]] + [sid_obj.polarity_scores(word)["compound"] for word in sentence.split()]
    })

def FLAIR_sentiment_scores(sentence): 
    flair_sentiment = flair.models.TextClassifier.load('en-sentiment')
    s = flair.data.Sentence(sentence)
    flair_sentiment.predict(s)
    total_sentiment = s.labels
    print(total_sentiment) 
    
    tokens = [token.text for token in s.tokens]
    ss = [flair.data.Sentence(s) for s in tokens]
    [flair_sentiment.predict(s) for s in ss]
    sentiments = [s.labels[0].score * (-1,1)[str(s.labels[0]).split()[0].startswith("POS")] for s in ss]
    
    visualise_sentiments({
      "Sentence":["SENTENCE"] + tokens,
      "Sentiment":[total_sentiment[0].score *(-1,1)[str(total_sentiment[0]).split()[0].startswith("POS")]] + sentiments,
    })

def extract_feature(file_name, mfcc, chroma, mel, zcr):
        with soundfile.SoundFile(file_name) as sound_file:
            X = sound_file.read(dtype="float32")
            sample_rate=sound_file.samplerate
            if chroma:
                stft=np.abs(librosa.stft(X))
            result=np.array([])
            #Chromagram
            if chroma:
                chroma=np.mean(librosa.feature.chroma_stft(S=stft, sr=sample_rate).T,axis=0)
                result=np.hstack((result, chroma))
            #Mel Frequency Cepstral Coefficents
            if mfcc:
                mfccs=np.mean(librosa.feature.mfcc(y=X, sr=sample_rate, n_mfcc=40).T, axis=0)
                result=np.hstack((result, mfccs))
            #Zero Crossing Point
            if zcr:
                mfccs=np.mean(librosa.feature.zero_crossing_rate(y=X).T, axis=0)
                result=np.hstack((result, mfccs))
            #Mel Frequency
            if mel:
                mel=np.mean(librosa.feature.melspectrogram(X, sr=sample_rate).T,axis=0)
                result=np.hstack((result, mel))
        return result

In [22]:
def load_data(test_size=0.25):
    x,y=[],[]
    for file in glob.glob("./VoiceDetection/dataset/Actor_*/*.wav"):
        file_name=os.path.basename(file)
        emotion=emotions[file_name.split("-")[2]]
        if emotion not in observed_emotions:
            continue
        feature=extract_feature(file, mfcc=True, chroma=True, mel=True, zcr = True)
        x.append(feature)
        y.append(emotion)
    
    return train_test_split(np.array(x), y, test_size=test_size, random_state=999)

def emotion (audio):
    record =[]
    for file in glob.glob(path+audio):
        feature=extract_feature(file, mfcc=True, chroma=True, mel=True, zcr =True)
        record.append(feature)
    record = np.array(record)
    
    prediction = model.predict(record)
    if prediction[0] in ('happy','surprised'):
        emo = emoji.emojize(':smiley:', use_aliases=True)
        label = "positive"
    else:
        emo = emoji.emojize(':rage:', use_aliases=True)
        label = "negative"
    print (label, emo)
